'''Michal Habai''' (born 30 July 1985) is a [[Slovakia]]n professional [[Association football|football]]er who plays as a defender for [[Greenock Morton F.C.|Greenock Morton]].

==Club career==
Habai came to [[Scotland]] at the age of 27, having spent his career playing in his homeland of [[Slovakia]], with a spell in the [[Czech Republic]] with [[Czech 2. Liga|Druh<U+00E1> liga]] side [[FK Ban<U+00ED>k Sokolov|Ban<U+00ED>k Sokolov]].

He signed for [[Greenock Morton F.C.|Greenock Morton]] in July 2013,<ref name="slovaks">{{cite news|url=http://www.greenocktelegraph.co.uk/sport/morton/articles/2013/07/19/465000-duo-sign-for-morton-/|title=Duo sign for Morton|publisher=Greenock Telegraph|first=Jonathan|last=Mitchell|date=19 July 2013|accessdate=19 July 2013}}</ref> and made his first competitive debut for [[Greenock Morton F.C.|Morton]] in a 1-0 defeat in the [[Scottish Challenge Cup]] to [[Annan Athletic F.C.|Annan Athletic]].

Habai turned down an approach from lower league side [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] as he preferred to play at a higher level in the [[Scottish Championship]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.greenocktelegraph.co.uk/sport/morton/articles/2013/07/24/465438-exclusive-michal-ignored-rangers-offer-/|title=EXCLUSIVE Michal ignored Rangers offer|publisher=Greenock Telegraph|first=Jonathan|last=Mitchell|date=24 July 2013|accessdate=27 July 2013}}</ref>

